=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_OnePole_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright gritty sound, with complex oscillator character around 52 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 52.0631
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.1012
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5317
  pitch_clarity: 12.1997
  inharmonicity: 0.0523
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.8926
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: OnePole Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/OnePole.html
// Tags: OnePole, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
{ OnePole.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.5), 0.95) }.play

{ OnePole.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.5), -0.95) }.play

{ OnePole.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.5), Line.kr(-0.99, 0.99, 10)) }.play
